'''''Star Wars Insider'' 75''' is the seventy-fifth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[April 6]], [[2004]]. The subscriber-exclusive edition of issue 75 included the seventh volume of ''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'', the [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Official ''Star Wars'' Fan Club]] newsletter.

==Contents==
*"[[Prequel Update]] for Episode III" {{C|by [[Jane Irene Kelly]]}}
*:<small>Late [[February]] was crunch time for production crew as they put the finishing touches on the "first assembly" of [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]].</small>
*"[[Appearing Knightley (and the Women of Star Wars)|Appearing Knightley (and the Women of ''Star Wars'')]]" {{C|by [[Gabriela Tscharner-Patao]] with [[Jim Swallow|James Swallow]], [[Mary Franklin]] and [[Peter Roberts]]}}
*:<small>Ever since her small role in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|Episode I]], [[Keira Knightley]]'s star has been on the rise. Learn what's next for the former [[Handmaiden/Legends|handmaiden]], and for eight other women on screen and behind the scenes for ''[[Star Wars]]'' movies.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in the Outlander Club: It's Ladies' Night]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>Never before have so many women appeared in one scene in a ''Star Wars'' movie. Now you can get their names, if not their numbers.</small>
*"[[Special Modifications: Steve Gawley on the Evolution of the Millennium Falcon|Special Modifications: Steve Gawley on the Evolution of the ''Millennium Falcon'']]" {{C|by [[Ron Magid]]}}
*:<small>Would [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] have been so cool if he'd flown the [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']] instead of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]?</small>
*"[[They Might Be Giants: A Tour of Gentle Giant Studios]]" {{C|by [[Eric Moro]]}}
*:<small>They'll take your face off and put it on another actor, or cast your likeness in resin with or without a [[Carbon-freezing chamber/Legends|carbon-freezing chamber]].</small>
*"[[Grievous Era: Unveiling the New Icon of Evil]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>He's so bad he can't wait for Episode III to start trouncing some [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. Meet [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]], part machine, part&hellip; something else.</small>
*"[[Or Die Trying]]" {{C|by [[Sean Williams]] with [[Shane Dix]]}}
*:<small>[[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] is on a mission to stop a [[Scientist/Legends|scientist]] from offering villains that most terrible weapon: eternal life.</small>

